race.description: Galloping Gourmet Tour Heading To Richmond Hcp  (C1)
race.comment: JENNI THE CAT (6) was scratched at the barrier in early December then finally got going just after Christmas and was a dominant winner storming home to score. Up in trip but has big upside and expected to go close again. BENEFICIARY (1) was strongly fancied at debut and gave nothing else a chance, leading throughout to score by a space. Looks promising and can go close again. BUNKER JAKO (3) wasn't far away two back then could manage only midfield and well held last time. Much better than that and worth another chance. AMAHLOSI (4) was only a couple of lengths away in sixth last time and has a nice weight drop with the claim. Can give a big sight off the low draw. THANKGODITSFRIDAY (10) ran 10th at big odds but was only 2.5 lengths from the winner at Hobart latest in what has proven a hot form race. Can run well at odds.
